strings : removeDuplicates

Write a method named removeDuplicates that accepts a string parameter and returns a new string with all consecutive occurrences of the same character in the string replaced by a single occurrence of that character. 
For example, the call of removeDuplicates("bookkeeeeeper") should return "bokeper".

  public static String removeDuplicates(String str) {
        ArrayList<Character> listOfStrings = new ArrayList<>();
        String stringWithDuplicatesRemoved = "";
        for(int i = 0; i < str.length(); i++) {
            listOfStrings.add(str.charAt(i));
        }
        for(int i = 0; i < listOfStrings.size() - 1; i++) {
            if (listOfStrings.get(i) == listOfStrings.get(i + 1)) {
                listOfStrings.remove(i);
                i--;
            }
        }
        for(int i = 0; i < listOfStrings.size(); i++) {
            stringWithDuplicatesRemoved += listOfStrings.get(i);
        }
        return stringWithDuplicatesRemoved;
    }


